Bugs Found:
1. Explanation: Potential null pointer exception in the fields() method when fields is null or empty
   Suggested Fix: fields(String... fields) {
    if (fields == null || fields.length == 0) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("specified fields can't be null or empty");
    }
    Set<String> fieldSet = new HashSet<>(Arrays.asList(fields));
    this.fields = fieldSet.toArray(new String[0]);
    return this;
}
2. Explanation: Missing null check for the indices parameter in the indices(String... indices) method
   Suggested Fix: public FieldCapabilitiesRequest indices(String... indices) {
    this.indices = Objects.requireNonNull(indices, "indices must not be null");
    return this;
}
3. Explanation: Potential security issue due to the inclusion of the includeIndices flag in the request
   Suggested Fix: Consider removing the includeIndices flag from the request or making it optional

